sses that influence resource allocation in a large assemblage of many species may result in statistical patterns of energy use and biomass that tend to maximize ecological quantities analogous to entropy in statistical physical systems. Key words: biomass; birds; body size; energetics; macroecology; resource allocation; species diversity; statistical distributions.},
